>>Having a heck of a time getting the tie rod off without the proper tool,
{heat and WD 40 haven't done it!)<<

go to your FLAPS & buy (or rent) one of those 'pickle fork' tools. apply
the heat to the tie rod end, insert pickle fork & bank away with a small
sledge.

